en_59807_0	Three high court judges have been appointed to the second permanent high court at-bar to hear high profile financial frauds and corruption cases.
en_59807_1	Chief Justice Priyasath Dep has made the appointments.
en_59807_2	The special trial-at-bar will comprise high court judges R Gurusinghe, Amal Ranaraja and Shashi Mahendran.
en_59807_3	The cabinet of Ministers had granted their approval for the establishment of three special high courts with an aim to speed up cases related to mass scale, corruption and financial misappropriation.
en_59807_4	The new courts were established by amending judicature bill under the recommendations of the Supreme Court.
en_59807_5	The first special high court is in operation currently.
